_pdbx_database_remark.id     999 
_pdbx_database_remark.text   
;SEQUENCE
The chimera protein consists of immunoglobulin light chain variable region (chains C, G), a linker GGGGSGGGGSGGGGS, and immunoglobulin heavy chain variable region (chains D, H). However, the linker GGGGSGGGGSGGGGS are not modeled due to disorder.
The conflicts are due to immunoglobulin domain variable region (v) 
;
